Identity theft is a crime that evolves with every advance in technology.
She had no idea what identity theft was until 1995, when she received a call from the Bank of New York demanding that Frank pay up on her $ 11,000 credit card balance.
According to a recent report by the U.S. General Accounting Office, the Secret Service estimates that $ 750 million was lost last year from identity theft, up from $ 450 million in 1996.
The Identity Theft and Assumption Deterrence Act of 1998 makes it a felony to commit identity theft.
